A skeleton setup for starting a django project with virtualenv and buildout.

Approximate steps to reproduce this repository:

$ virtualenv2.6 --no-site-packages my-django-skeleton
$ cd my-django-skeleton
$ source ./bin/activate
$ mkdir -p src/skeleton
$ touch LICENSE (or create it from http://www.opensource.org/licenses/bsd-license.php)
$ touch README
$ touch src/skeleton/__init__.py
$ cat - > buildout.cfg
[buildout]
parts =
^D
$ touch setup.py
$ curl -O http://svn.zope.org/*checkout*/zc.buildout/trunk/bootstrap/bootstrap.py
$ git init
$ cat - > .gitignore
*.pyc
*.pyo
.installed.cfg
.Python
bin
develop-eggs
dist
downloads
eggs
include
lib
parts
src/*.egg-info
^D
$ python bootstrap.py

[Based on http://jacobian.org/writing/django-apps-with-buildout/]
